Error: One Potential Error That A Beginner May Encounter When Using The Pterodactyl Panel For Their Minecraft Server Is An Issue With Server Memory Allocation. This Error May Manifest As Lag, Crashes, Or Other Performance Issues.

Step-By-Step

Solution: 1. Log in to your Pterodactyl panel and navigate to the server you are having trouble with.
2. Click on the "Console" tab and enter the server command: "java -Xms<amount of memory>G -Xmx
